headline: How Strong Earnings, Record Accounts and Stablecoin Funding At Interactive Brokers (IBKR) Has Changed Its Investment Story
summary: Interactive Brokers Group reported past fourth-quarter 2025 net income of US$284 million and full-year net income of US$984 million, alongside a US$0.08 quarterly dividend and new stablecoin funding for eligible accounts. Record client growth, rising client equity to US$780 billion, and expanded global and digital access underscore how Interactive Brokers is broadening its brokerage platform’s reach. Against this backdrop, we’ll examine how the strong earnings and record account growth shape...
